The Federal Government has named the Idu railway complex after the Deputy Secretary-General of the United Nations, Mrs. Amina Mohammed. Mr. Eric Ojiekwe, the Director, Press and Public Relations, Ministry of Transportation, disclosed this in a statement on Tuesday in Abuja. According to Ojiekwe, the complex, including its train station and the light train station of the Federal Capital Territory and all its Facilities have been named after the UN official, “It has also gained the concurrence of the Minister of Transportation, Mr. Rotimi Amaechi, and the Minister of the Federal Capital Territory, Mr. Mohammed Bello.” (NAN)